ag|Yemen}}\n|[[Islamic architecture|Islamic]]\n|2008\n|-\n|'''[[CMH Masjid Jhelum]]'''\n|[[File:CMH_Mosque.JPG|160px|center]]\t\n|{{nts|25000}}<ref name=\"CMH\">{{cite web|title=JHELUM- THE CITY OF SOLDIERS|url=https://jhelum.pk/jhelum-the-city-of-soldiers/|publisher=Delhi Tourism|accessdate=12 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180802002602/https://jhelum.pk/jhelum-the-city-of-soldiers/|archive-date=2 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|\n|[[Jhelum Cantt]]\n|{{flag|Pakistan}}\n|[[Mughal architecture|Mughal]]\n|1950<ref name=\"CMH\"/>\t\n|-\n|[[Jama Masjid, Delhi|'''Jama Masjid''']]\n{{lang-hi|\u091c\u093e\u092e\u093e \u092e\u0938\u094d\u091c\u093f\u0926}}\n\n{{lang-ur|{{Nastaliq|\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639 \u0645\u0633\u062c\u062f}}|size=70%}}\n|[[File:Jama Masjid, Delhi.jpg|160px|center]]\n|{{nts|25000}}<ref>{{cite web|title=Charming Chadni Chowk|url=http://delhitourism.gov.in/delhitourism/pdf/Small-walk.pdf|publisher=Delhi Tourism|accessdate=23 March 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402100019/http://delhitourism.gov.in/delhitourism/pdf/Small-walk.pdf|archive-date=2 April 2015|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|\n|[[Central Delhi]]\n|{{flag|India}}\n|[[Mughal architecture|Mughal]]\n|1656\n|-\n|'''[[Sultan Salahuddin Abdul Aziz Mosque]]'''\n{{lang-ms|Masjid Sultan Salahuddin Abdul Aziz}}\n\n[[Jawi alphabet|Jawi]]: \u0645\u0633\u062c\u062f \u0633\u0644\u0637\u0627\u0646 \u0635\u0644\u0627\u062d\u064f \u0627\u0644\u062f\u064a\u0646 \u0639\u0628\u062f\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0632\u064a\u0632\n\n{{lang-zh|c=\u82cf\u4e39\u6c99\u62c9\u80e1\u6c40\u963f\u90fd\u963f\u5179\u6c99\u56de\u6559\u5802|s=|t=|Masjid Dian Al-Mahri}}\n\n{{lang-ta|\u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bb2\u0bbe\u0bb9\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b85\u0baa\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bb8\u0bc0\u0bb8\u0bcd \u0bae\u0b9a\u0bc2\u0ba4\u0bbf}}\n|[[File:SultanSalahuddinMosque1.jpg|160px|center]]\n|{{nts|24000}}<ref name=\"Ir\">[http://www.iranreview.org/content/Documents/Iran-s-Mosques-The-Most-Beautiful-in-the-World.htm Iran's Mosques: The Most Beautiful in the World] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190212190351/http://www.iranreview.org/content/Documents/Iran-s-Mosques-The-Most-Beautiful-in-the-World.htm |date=12 February 2019 }}. ''Iran Review''. Retrieved 12 February 2019.</ref>\n|\n|[[Shah Alam]]\n| {{flag|Malaysia}}\n|[[Malay Architecture|Malay]], [[Modern architecture|Modern]]\n|1988\n|-\n|'''[[Masjid Al-Dahab]]'''\n{{lang-fil|Moskeng Ginto}}\n|[[File:Golden Mosque 10.JPG|160px|center]]\n|{{nts|22000}}<ref name=\"identity in crossroad\">{{cite journal | author=Angeles, Vivienne | title=Constructing Identity: Visual Expressions of Islam in the Predominantly Catholic Philippines | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=N_Jkjk2Tec4C&pg=PA204&dq=quiapo%2Bmosque&hl=en&sa=X&ei=Z6SIU8H8B8eF8gXRn4DIAw&ved=0CD8Q6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=quiapo%2Bmosque&f=false | work=Identity in Crossroad Civilisations: Ethnicity, Nationalism and Globalism in Asia | pages= 195\u2013218 | publisher= Amsterdam University Press| year=2009}}</ref>\n|\n|[[Manila]]\n|{{flag|Philippines}}\n|[[Architecture of the Philippines|Maranao]], [[Architecture of the Philippines|Maguindanao]], [[Architecture of the Philippines|Tausug]]\n|1976\n|-\n|'''[[Al-Azhar Mosque]]'''\n{{lang-ar|\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0623\u0632\u0647\u0640\u0631|}}\n|[[File:Cairo - Islamic district - Al Azhar Mosque and University.JPG|160px|center]]\n|{{nts|20000}}<ref name=\"pu\"/>\n| \n|[[Cairo]]\n| {{flag|Egypt}}\n|[[Fatimid architecture|Fatimid]]\n|{{sort|0972|972}}\n|-\n|'''[[Dian Al-Mahri Mosque]]'''\n{{lang-id|Masjid Dian Al-Mahri}}\n\n{{lang-su|{{sund|\u1b99\u1b9e\u1baa\u1b8f\u1ba4\u1b93\u1baa \u1b83\u1b9c\u1baa-\u1b99\u1b82\u1b9b\u1ba4}}}}\n|[[File:Masjid Dian Al-Mahri.jpg|160px|center]]\n|{{nts|20000}}<ref>[http://www.pikiran-rakyat.com/cetak/2007/022007/10/pakuan/bogorraya02.htm \"Masjid Berkubah Emas\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://