le.com/extreme/en/islam-artefacts/sultanahmet-camii.htm Sultanahmet Camii] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190213005528/http://www.orangesmile.com/extreme/en/islam-artefacts/sultanahmet-camii.htm |date=13 February 2019 }}. ''Orange Smile''. Retrieved 12 February 2019.</ref>\n|\n|[[Istanbul]]\n|{{flag|Turkey}}\n|[[Ottoman architecture#Classical period (1437\u20131703)|Late Classical Ottoman]]\n|1616\n|-\n|'''[[T\u00fcrkmenba\u015fy Ruhy Mosque]]'''\n{{lang-tk|T\u00fcrkmenba\u015fy Ruhy Metjidi}}\n|[[File:Ashgabat mosque IMG 5749 (25838304790).jpg|160px|center]]\n|{{nts|10000}}<ref>{{cite news|last=Corley|first=Felix|title=TURKMENISTAN: 2004, the year of demolished mosques|url=http://www.forum18.org/Archive.php?article_id=481|accessdate=25 May 2012|newspaper=Forum 18 News Service|date=4 January 2005|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120208163755/http://www.forum18.org/Archive.php?article_id=481|archive-date=8 February 2012|url-status=live}}</ref> \n|\n|[[Gypjak]]\n|{{flag|Turkmenistan}}\n|[[Islamic architecture|Islamic]]\n|2004\n|-\n|'''[[UGM Campus Mosque]]'''\n{{lang-id|Masjid Kampus UGM}}\n\n{{lang-jv|\ua9a9\ua9bc\ua9b1\ua9c0\ua997\ua9b6\ua9a2\ua9c0\ua991\ua9a9\ua9c0\ua9a5\ua9b8\ua9b1\ua9c0\ua988\ua992\ua9ba\ua98c\ua9a9\ua9c0}}\n|[[File:After_ied_fitri_praying_@_UGM_mosque_Yogya_-_panoramio.jpg|160px|center]]\n|{{nts|10000}}<ref>[http://duniamasjid.islamic-center.or.id/693/masjid-kampus-ugm/ Masjid Kampus UGM] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190213005602/http://duniamasjid.islamic-center.or.id/693/masjid-kampus-ugm/ |date=13 February 2019 }}. ''Dunia Masjid''. Retrieved 12 February 2019.</ref>\n|\n|[[Sleman Regency]]\n|{{flag|Indonesia}}\n|[[Modern architecture|Modern]], [[Chinese architecture|Chinese]]\n|1999\n|-\n|'''[[Imam Husayn Shrine]]'''\n{{lang-ar|\u0645\u064e\u0642\u0640\u0627\u0645 \u0627\u0644\u0625\u0645\u0640\u0627\u0645 \u0627\u0644\u0640\u062d\u0640\u0633\u0640\u064a\u0640\u0646 \u0627\u0628\u0640\u0646 \u0639\u0640\u0644\u064a|}}\n|[[File:Kerbela Hussein Moschee.jpg|160px|center]]\n|\n|{{nts|8597}}<ref>{{cite encyclopedia|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YVYkrNhPMQkC&pg=PA307|first=Linda Kay|last=Davidson|encyclopedia=Pilgrimage: From the Ganges to Graceland|title=Karbala (Iraq)|date=2002|pp=306\u2013307|quote=The mosque was again rebuilt with an 83-by-109-meter courtyard.}}</ref>\n|[[Karbala]]\n|{{flag|Iraq}}\n|[[Islamic architecture|Islamic]]\n|{{sort|0680|680}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==See also==\n{{Mosques}}\n* [[Islamic architecture]]\n* [[Holiest sites in Islam]]\n* [[Lists of mosques]]\n** [[Jama Masjid]]\n** [[List of mosques]]\n** [[List of the oldest mosques]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n{{GeoGroupTemplate}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n{{List of mosques}}\n{{Religion-related lists of superlative buildings}}\n{{Structural extremes}}\n\n[[Category:Lists of mosques| Largest]]\n[[Category:Religion-related lists of superlatives]]\n[[Category:Lists of largest buildings and structures]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2017}}\n{{More citations needed|date=February 2019}}\n\nA [[mosque]], or ''masjid'' ({{lang-ar|\u0645\u064e\u0640\u0633\u0652\u0640\u062c\u0650\u0640\u062f}}), is a place of worship for [[Muslims]]. Mosques have the capacity to accommodate numerous worshippers for prayer services known as ''[[Salah]]''. Some mosques that are destinations for pilgrimages are also some of the largest mosques in the world \u2014 the largest mosque in the world by area is the [[Imam Reza Shrine]] in [[Mashhad]], [[Iran]], which is a site of pilgrimage for [[Imam Reza]]. All the mosques in this list are also known as [[Jama Masjid]], a type of mosque designed to accommodate the Friday congregational prayer known as ''[[jummah]]''. \n\nThis list lists mosques all over the world that can accommodate at least 100,000 worshipers. Some mosques provide information on the capacity of worshippers it can accommodate in different prayer spaces, such as prayer hall, [[courtyard]] known as ''[[sahn]]'', and [[portico]]. For these mosques, indicated capacity is a sum of all the available prayer spaces. Mosques listed here are of any [[Islamic schools and branches|religious branch]] which regards themselves as Muslim.\n\n==List==\n{{Expand list|date=January 2009}}\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Name\n!class=unsortable|Images\n!Capacity\n!Area (m<sup>2</sup>)\n!City\n!Country\n!Architectural style\n!Year of first building\n|-\n|'''[[Imam Reza Shrine]]'''\n{{lang-fa|{{Nastaliq|\u062d\u0631\u0645 \u0627\u0645\u0627\u0645 \u0631\u0636\u0627}}|size=70%}}\n|[[File:RezaShrine.jpg|160px|center]]\n|{{nts|1500000}}<ref name=\"At\">{{cite web|url=https://largest.org/culture/mosques/|title=7 Largest Mosques in the World|work=Largest.org|accessdate=4 December 2018}}</ref>\n|{{nts|598657}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.imamreza.net/eng/imamreza.php?id=1073|title=The Glory of the Islamic World|work=Imam Reza (A.S.) Network|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100612095542/http://imamreza.net/eng/imamreza.php?id=1073|archivedate=12 June 2010|url-status=dead|accessdate=25 May 2009|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|[[Mashhad]]\n|{{flag|Iran}}\n|[[Iranian architecture|Iranian]]\n|{{sort|0729|729}}\n|-\n|'''[[Great Mosque of Mecca]]'''\n{{lang-ar|\u0671\u0644\u0645\u0640\u0633\u0640\u062c\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0640\u062d\u0640\u0631\u0627\u0645|links=no|}}\n|[[File:A packed house - Flickr - Al Jazeera English.jpg|160px|center]]\n|{{nts|1500000}}<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://blog.realestate.cornell.edu/2018/03/21/grandmosqueexpansion/|title=Grand Mosque Expansion Highlights Growth of Saudi Arabian Tourism Industry (6 mins)|last=Daye|first=Ali|date=21 March 2018|website=Cornell Real Estate Review|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190209180524/https://blog.realestate.cornell.edu/2018/03/21/grandmosqueexpansion/|archive-date=9 February 2019|url-status=live|access-date=9 February 2019}