-II}}\n|[[File:Mosqu\u00e9e hassan II - Photo de Abdellatif AMAJGAG.jpg|frameless|164x164px]]\n|{{nts|105000}}{{efn|name=HassanII|Capacity, inside: 25,000; outside: 80,000<ref>{{cite web|url=http://architecture.about.com/od/greatbuildings/ig/Sacred-Buildings/Hassan-II-Mosque-.htm|title=Sacred Buildings|author=Jackie Craven|work=About.com Home|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110606153039/http://architecture.about.com/od/greatbuildings/ig/Sacred-Buildings/Hassan-II-Mosque-.htm|archivedate=6 June 2011|url-status=live|accessdate=15 March 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref>}}\n|\n|[[Casablanca]]\n|{{flag|Morocco}}\n|[[Moorish architecture|Moorish]], [[Moroccan architecture|Moroccan]]\n|1993\n|-\n|'''[[Badshahi Mosque]]'''\n{{lang-ur|{{Nastaliq|\u0628\u0627\u062f\u0634\u0627\u06c1\u06cc \u0645\u0633\u062c\u062f}}|size=70%}}\n|[[File:Badshahi Mosque July 1 2005 pic32 by Ali Imran (1).jpg|160px|center]]\n|{{nts|100000}}<ref>[http://www.pakistantoursguide.com/badshahi-mosque.html Badshahi Mosque with a capacity of 100'000 is Pakistan's second largest Mosque] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190414183405/http://www.pakistantoursguide.com/badshahi-mosque.html |date=14 April 2019 }}. ''Pakistan Tours Guide''. Retrieved April 14, 2019.</ref>\n|\n|[[Lahore]]\n| {{flag|Pakistan}}\n|[[Mughal architecture|Mughal]]\n|1673\n|-\n|'''[[Chota Imambara]]'''\n{{lang-hi|\u091b\u094b\u091f\u093e \u0907\u092e\u093e\u092e\u092c\u093e\u0921\u093c\u093e}}]\n\n{{lang-ur|{{Nastaliq|\u0686\u06be\u0648\u0679\u0627 \u0627\u0645\u0627\u0645\u0628\u0627\u0691\u0627}}|size=70%}}\n|[[File:Chhota imambara gate.jpg|160px|center]]\n|{{nts|100000}}{{Citation needed|date=February 2019}}\n|\n|[[Lucknow]]\n|{{flag|India}}\n|[[Mughal architecture|Mughal]]\n|1784\n|-\n|'''[[Grand Jamia Mosque, Lahore|Grand Jamia Mosque]]'''\n{{lang-ur|{{Nastaliq|\u06af\u0631\u06cc\u0646\u0688 \u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639 \u0645\u0633\u062c\u062f}}|size=70%}}\n|[[File:Grand_Jamia_Masjid_Bahria_Town_Lahore_Pakistan_cropped.j