gory:History of Kuban]]\n[[Category:Khaganates]]\n[[Category:Khanates of the North Caucasus]]\n[[Category:Turkic peoples of Europe]]\n[[Category:States and territories established in the 650s]]\n[[Category:States and territories disestablished in the 960s]]\n[[Category:Jewish polities]]\n[[Category:Saltovo-Mayaki culture]]\n", "name_user": "Matthewrbowker", "label": "safe", "comment": "Notes fix", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Khazars"}
{"title_page": "1997 Stinkers Bad Movie Awards", "text_new": "{{short description|Award ceremony presented by the Stinkers Bad Movie Awards in 1997}}\n{{Infobox film awards\n| number           = 20\n| award            = Stinkers Bad Movie Awards\n| date             = 1998\n| film             =''[[Batman and Robin (film)|Batman and Robin]]''\n| most_wins        =''[[Batman and Robin (film)|Batman and Robin]]'' (4)\n| most_nominations =''[[Batman and Robin (film)|Batman and Robin]]'' (5)\n| last             = 1996\n| next             = 1998\n}}\n\nThe '''20th [[Stinkers Bad Movie Awards]]''' were released by the Hastings Bad Cinema Society in 1998 to honour the worst films the film industry had to offer in 1997. This was the first year that the ballots would be open to the public, which is why percentages of votes for each candidate were listed besides most categories. To celebrate the 20th award ballot, the Lifetime Non-Achievement Award was given out to [[Chevy Chase]] and a multitude of other categories, including Worst On-Screen Couple and Worst Director, were introduced. Founder Ray Wright listed ''Batman and Robin'' and ''Crash '' among his five worst movies of the 1990s, which also included ''[[It's Pat]]'', ''[[Pokemon: The First Movie]]'', and ''[[Nothing but Trouble (1991 film)|Nothing but Trouble]]''. While ''Batman and Robin'' was a preliminary target and took home several awards, ''Crash '' was largely ignored aside from the Founders Award because it was a low-key indie film.<ref>{{cite web |title=Q & A with the Stinkers |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20010413025218/http://thestinkers.com/qanda.html |website=The Stinkers |accessdate=29 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Thompson |first=Gary |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1298&dat=19980228&id=Ae0yAAAAIBAJ&sjid=VwgGAAAAIBAJ&pg=3861,5389515 |title=Group Recognzes Stinkers |accessdate=2013-03-31 |publisher=[[The Free Lance-Star]]|date=February 28, 1998}}</ref>\n\nListed as follows are the different categories with their respective winners and nominees, including Worst Picture and its dishonourable mentions, which are films that were considered for Worst Picture but ultimately failed to make the final ballot (30 total). All winners are highlighted.\n\n== Winners and Nominees ==\n\n=== Worst Picture ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n! Film<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20070103154753/http://theenvelope.latimes.com/extras/lostmind/year/1997/1997st.htm</ref>\n! class=\"unsortable\"|Production company(s)\n! Percentage of Votes\n|- style=\"background:#FAEB86\"\n| '''''[[Batman and Robin (film)|Batman and Robin]]'''''\n| '''[[Warner Bros.]]'''\n| '''43%'''\n|-\n| ''[[The Fifth Element]]''\n| [[Columbia Pictures|Sony]]\n| 12%\n|-\n|- style=\"background:#eee;\"\n| ''[[Lost Highway (film)|Lost Highway]]''\n| [[Universal Pictures]], [[October Films]]\n| 8%\n|-\n| ''[[The Postman (film)|The Postman]]''\n| [[Warner Bros.]]\n| 18%\n|-\n|- style=\"background:#eee;\"\n| ''[[Starship Troopers (film)|Starship Troopers]]''\n| [[TriStar Pictures|Sony]]\n| 19%\n|-\n|}\n\n==== Dishonourable Mentions ====\n{{div col|colwidth=32em}}\n* ''[[Alien Resurrection]]'' ([[20th Century Fox|Fox]])\n* ''[[An American Werewolf in Paris]]'' ([[Hollywood Pictures|Hollywood]])\n* ''[[Anaconda (film)|Anaconda]]'' ([[Columbia Pictures|Sony]])\n* ''[[B.A.P.S.]]'' ([[New Line Cinema|New Line]])\n* ''[[Bean (film)|Bean]]'' ([[Gramercy Pictures|Gramercy]])\n* ''[[Booty Call]]'' ([[Columbia Pictures|Sony]])\n* ''[[Con Air]]'' ([[Touchstone Pictures|Touchstone]])\n* ''[[Double Team (film)|Double Team]]'' ([[Columbia Pictures|Sony]])\n* ''[[Excess Baggage (1997 film)|Excess Baggage]]'' ([[Columbia Pictures|Sony]])\n* ''[[Face/Off]]'' ([[Paramount Pictures|Paramount]])\n* ''[[Father's Day (1997 film)|Father's Day]]'' ([[Warner Bros.]])\n* ''[[Fire Down Below (1997 film)|Fire Down Below]]'' ([[Warner Bros.]])\n* ''[[Flubber (film)|Flubber]]'' ([[Walt Disney Pictures|Disney