table sortable plainrowheaders\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\" align=\"centre\"\n! Recipient\n! Percentage of Votes\n|-\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\"\n| '''[[Jon Voight]] for ''[[Anaconda (film)|Anaconda]]'' and ''[[Most Wanted (1997 film)|Most Wanted]]'''''\n| '''31%'''\n|-\n|[[Richard Gere]] in ''[[The Jackal (1997 film)|The Jackal]]''\n| 19%\n|-\n|[[Frances McDormand]] in ''[[Paradise Road (1997 film)|Paradise Road]]''\n| 10%\n|-\n|[[Viggo Mortensen]] in ''[[G.I. Jane]]''\n| 13%\n|-\n|[[Brad Pitt]] in ''[[The Devil's Own]]'' and ''[[Seven Years in Tibet (1997 film)|Seven Years in Tibet]]''\n| 27%\n|-\n|}\n\n==== Most Painfully Unfunny Comedy ====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\" align=\"centre\"\n! Recipient\n! Percentage of Votes\n|-\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\"\n| '''''[[8 Heads in a Duffel Bag]]'' ([[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer|MGM]], [[Orion Pictures|Orion]])'''\n| '''26%'''\n|-\n|''[[Father's Day (1997 film)|Father's Day]]'' ([[Warner Bros.]])\n| 25%\n|-\n|''[[Gone Fishin' (film)|Gone Fishin']]'' ([[Hollywood Pictures|Hollywood]])\n| 16%\n|-\n|''[[Mr. Magoo (film)|Mr. Magoo]]'' ([[Walt Disney Pictures|Disney]])\n| 19%\n|-\n|''[[RocketMan]]'' ([[Walt Disney Pictures|Disney]])\n| 14%\n|-\n|}\n\n==== Most Unwelcome Direct-to-Video Release ====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\" align=\"centre\"\n! Recipient\n! Percentage of Votes\n|-\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\"\n| '''''Pamela Anderson Lee's Homemade Porno Video'''''\n| '''35%'''\n|-\n|''[[Love in Paris|Another 9 1/2 Weeks]]''\n| 24%\n|-\n|''[[Casper: A Spirited Beginning]]''\n| 10%\n|-\n|''[[Ernest Goes to Africa]]''\n| 16%\n|-\n|''[[The Land Before Time V: The Mysterious Island]]''\n| 15%\n|-\n|}\n\n==== Lifetime Non-Achievement Award - The Hall of Shame ====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\" align=\"centre\"\n! Recipient\n! Percentage of Votes\n|-\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\"\n| '''[[Chevy Chase]]'''\n| '''37%'''\n|-\n|[[Mel Brooks]]\n| 13%\n|-\n|[[Whoopi Goldberg]]\n| 26%\n|-\n|[[Burt Reynolds]]\n| 24%\n|-\n|}\n\n==== The Founders Award - What Were They Thinking and Why? ====\n* '''''[[Cats Don't Dance]]'' ([[Warner Bros.]])'''\n* '''''[[Crash (1996 film)|Crash]]'' ([[Fine Line Features|Fine Line]])'''\n* '''''[[Jungle 2 Jungle]]'' ([[Walt Disney Pictures|Disney]])'''\n* '''''[[Year of the Horse]]'' ([[Universal Pictures|Universal]], [[October Films|October]])'''<ref>{{cite web |title=1997's Biggest Studio Disgraces |url=https://web.archive.org/web/19991010130006/http://thestinkers.com/founders_award.html |website=The Stinkers |accessdate=6 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Stinkers Bad Movie Awards |state=autocollapse}}\n\n[[Category:Stinkers Bad Movie Awards]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Award ceremony presented by the Stinkers Bad Movie Awards in 1997}}\n{{Infobox film awards\n| number           = 20\n| award            = Stinkers Bad Movie Awards\n| date             = 1998\n| film             =''[[Batman and Robin (film)|Batman and Robin]]''\n| most_wins        =''[[Batman and Robin (film)|Batman and Robin]]'' (4)\n| most_nominations =''[[Batman and Robin (film)|Batman and Robin]]'' (5)\n| last             = 1996\n| next             = 1998\n}}\n\nThe '''20th [[Stinkers Bad Movie Awards]]''' were released by the Hastings Bad Cinema Society in 1998 to honour the worst films the film industry had to offer in 1997. This was the first year that the ballots would be open to the public, which is why percentages of votes for each candidate were listed besides most categories. To celebrate the 20th award ballot, the Lifetime Non-Achievement Award was given out to [[Chevy Chase]] and a multitude of other categories, including Worst On-Screen Couple and Worst Director, were introduced. Founder Ray Wright listed ''Batman and Robin'' and ''Crash '' among his five worst movies of the 1990s, which also included ''[[It's Pat]]'', ''[[Pokemon: The First Movie]]'', and ''[[Nothing but Trouble (1991 film)|Nothing but Trouble]]''. While ''Batman and Robin'' was a preliminary target and took home several awards, ''Crash '' was largely ignored aside from the Founders Award because it was a low-key indie film.<ref>{{cite web |title=Q & A with the Stinkers |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20010413025218/http://thestinkers.com/qanda.html |website=The Stinkers |accessdate=29 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Thompson |first=Gary |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1298&dat=19980228&id=Ae0yAAAAIBAJ&sjid=VwgGAAAAIBAJ&pg=3861,5389515 |title=Group Recognzes Stinkers |accessdate=2013-03-31 |publisher=[[The Free Lance-Star]]|date=February 28, 1998}}</ref>\n\nListed as follows are the different categories with their respective winners and nominees, including Worst Picture and its dishonourable mentions, which are films that were considered for Worst Picture but ultimately failed to make the final ballot (30 total). All winners are highlighted.\n\n== Winners and Nominees ==\n\n=== Worst Picture ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n! Film<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20070103154753/http://theenvelope.latimes.com/extras/lostmind/year/1997/1997st.htm</ref>\n! class=\"unsortable\"|Production company(s)\n! Percentage of Votes\n|- style=\"background:#FAEB86\"\n| '''''[[Batman and Robin (film)|Batman and Robin]]'''''\n| '''[[Warner Bros.]]'''\n| '''43%'''\n|-\n| ''[[The Fifth Element]]''\n| [[Columbia Pictures|Sony]]\n| 12%\n|-\n|- style=\"background:#eee;\"\n| ''[[Lost Highway (film)|Lost Highway]]''\n| [[Universal Pictures]], [[October Films]]\n| 8%\n|-\n| ''[[The Postman (film)|The Postman]]''\n| [[Warner Bros.]]\n| 18%\n|-\n|- style=\"background:#eee;\"\n| ''[[Starship Troopers (film)|Starship Troopers]]''\n| [[TriStar Pictures|Sony]]\n| 19%\n|-\n|}\n\n==== Dishonourable Mentions ====\n{{div col|colwidth=32em}}\n* ''[[Alien Resurrection]]'' ([[20th Century Fox|Fox]])\n* ''[[An American Werewolf in Paris]]'' ([[Hollywood Pictures|Hollywood]])\n* ''[[Anaconda (film)|Anaconda]]'' ([[Columbia Pictures|Sony]])\n* ''[[B.A.P.S.]]'' ([[New Line Cinema|New Line]])\n* ''[[Bean (film)|Bean]]'' ([[Gramercy Pictures|Gramercy]])\n* ''[[Booty Call]]'' ([[Columbia Pictures|Sony]])\n* ''[[Con Air]]'' ([[Touchstone Pictures|Touchstone]])\n* ''[[Double Team (film)|Double Team]]'' ([[Columbia Pictures|Sony]])\n* ''[[Excess Baggage (1997 film)|Excess Baggage]]'' ([[Columbia Pictures|Sony]])\n* ''[[Face/Off]]'' ([[Paramount Pictures|Paramount]])\n* ''[[Father's Day (1997 film)|Father's Day]]'' ([[Warner Bros.]])\n* ''[[Fire Down Below (1997 film)|Fire Down Below]]'' ([[Warner Bros.]])\n* ''[[Flubber (film)|Flubber]]'' ([[Walt Disney Pictures|Disney]])\n* ''[[For Richer or Poorer]]'' ([[Universal Pictures|Universal]])\n* ''[[Free Willy 3]]'' ([[Warner Bros.]])\n* ''[[Gone Fishin' (film)|Gone Fishin']]'' ([[Hollywood Pictures|Hollywood]])\n* ''[[Home Alone 3]]'' ([[20th Century Fox|Fox]])\n* ''[[I Know What You Did Last Summer]]'' ([[Columbia Pictures|Sony]])\n* ''[[Jungle 2 Jungle]]'' ([[Walt Disney Pictures|Disney]])\n* ''[[McHale's Navy (1997 film)|McHale's Navy]]'' ([[Universal Pictures|Universal]])\n* ''[[Mr. Magoo (film)|Mr. Magoo]]'' ([[Walt Disney Pictures|Disney]])\n* ''[[The Pest (1997 film)|The Pest]]'' ([[TriStar Pictures|Sony]])\n* ''[[RocketMan]]'' ([[Walt Disney Pictures|Disney]])\n* ''[[A Smile Like Yours]]'' ([[Paramount Pictures|Paramount]])\n* ''[[Speed 2: Cruise Control]]'' ([[20th Century Fox|Fox]])\n* ''[[Steel (1997 film)|Steel]]'' ([[Warner Bros.]])\n* ''[['Til There Was You]]'' ([[Paramount Pictures|Paramount]])\n* ''[[Turbulence (1997 film)|Turbulence]]'' ([[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer|MGM]])\n* ''[[U Turn (1997 film)|U Turn]]'' ([[TriStar Pictures|Sony]])\n* ''[[Vegas Vacation]]'' ([[Warner Bros.]])\n{{div col end}}\n\n=== Other Categories ===\n\n==== Worst Director ====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\" align=\"centre\"\n! Recipient\n! Percentage of Votes\n|-\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\"\n| '''[[Joel Schumacher]] for ''[[Batman and Robin (film)|Batman and Robin]]'''''\n| '''33%'''\n|-\n|[[Luc Besson]] for ''[[The Fifth Element]]''\n| 7%\n|-\n|[[Kevin Costner]] for ''[[The Postman (film)|The Postman]]''\n| 22%\n|-\n|[[Jan de Bont]] for ''[[Speed 2: Cruise Control]]''\n| 29%\n|-\n|[[David Lynch]] for ''[[Lost Highway (film)|Lost Highway]]''\n| 9%\n|-\n|}\n\n==== Worst Actor ====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\" align=\"centre\"\n! Recipient\n! Percentage of Votes\n|-\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\"\n| '''[[Tom Arnold (actor)|Tom Arnold]] for ''[[McHale's Navy (1997 film)|McHale's Navy]]'''''\n| '''37%'''\n|-\n|[[John Leguizamo]] for ''[[The Pest (1997 film)|The Pest]]''\n| 17%\n|-\n|[[Joe Pesci]] for ''[[Gone Fishin' (film)|Gone Fishin']]''\n| 12%\n|-\n|[[Steven Seagal]] for ''[[Fire Down Below (1997 film)|Fire Down Below]]''\n| 24%\n|-\n|[[John Travolta]] for ''[[Mad City (film)|Mad City]]''\n| 10%\n|-\n|}\n\n==== Worst Actress ====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\" align=\"centre\"\n! Recipient\n! Percentage of Votes\n|-\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\"\n| '''[[Alicia Silverstone]] for ''[[Excess Baggage (1997 film)|Excess Baggage]]'''''\n| '''30%'''\n|-\n|[[Halle Berry]] for ''[[B.A.P.S.]]''\n| 28%\n|-\n|[[Lauren Holly]] for ''[[Turbulence (1997 film)|Turbulence]]''\n| 18%\n|-\n|[[Bette Midler]] for ''[[That Old Feeling (film)|That Old Feeling]]''\n| 13%\n|-\n|[[Sigourney Weaver]] for ''[[Alien Resurrection]]''\n| 11%\n|-\n|}\n\n==== Worst Supporting Actor ====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\" align=\"centre\"\n! Recipient\n! Percentage